  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (COMPOUND-03 adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification was performed across all five flow-speed combinations; mesh-convergence studies and solver verification activities were documented. The assessment team concluded that the body of evidence, taken in aggregate, supports a Medium assurance level and that the model is fit for the intended regulatory submission. Decision: Accepted. NOTE (adversarial): the declared assuranceLevel of 'Medium' is inconsistent with the structural evidence — the Discretization error factor carries achievedLevel 2 against requiredLevel 4, a Critical gap under W-AR-02, which precludes any assurance level above Low.",
  "couName": "VAD use",
  "decision": "Accepted",
  "assuranceLevel": "Medium",
  "deviceClass": "Class III",
  "modelRiskLevel": 5,
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/vad-hemolysis-mrl5",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/vad-hemolysis-absolute-threshold",
