    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment team reviewed all 13 credibility factors and the associated validation evidence. While several factors achieved levels below their required levels, the team concluded that the Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification provides sufficient coverage of the predictive uncertainty and that the aggregate body of evidence supports a Medium assurance level. The hemolysis predictions at design-point conditions are within ±35% of bench measurements, and the 72% probability of remaining below the clinical threshold was judged adequate for regulatory submission. The discretization error gap in the NIH scalar was noted but considered bounded by the uncertainty quantification envelope. Decision: Accepted at Medium assurance.",
